</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A738EEB56860690691BFA9DAFD8F1944" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">
<bibRefCitation id="6BAD17BA2C41343069D27A3F356DA2E1" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Berlingianis, Lund" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" refId="B19" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1845. Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano. Berlingianis, Lund, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.66977" title="Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano." url="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" year="1845">Dahlbom (1845)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="2758B559CED7754B8EAFD18F54D7C065" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum wesmaeli" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wesmaeli">
<emphasis id="4A43C8D72764D791619F4354A030B69A" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum wesmaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any note on the type series. More information can be found in his monographical work (
<bibRefCitation id="3BEC7678C7CCCF193318EBBF4AA530FE" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" refId="B21" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1854. Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta. Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.15890" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta" url="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" year="1854">Dahlbom 1854</bibRefCitation>
: 359): &quot; 
<emphasis id="A21C95F325929C9BF1E182BC3022781A" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Habitat in insula Rhodo; specimen unicum e Mus. Reg. Acad. Scient. Stockholm. communicavit Dom. Boheman</emphasis>
.&quot;. Currently there are three specimens in the collection collected on Rhodes by Hedenborg. Only one has a different printed label [Hedb.] [NHRS-HEVA000001129] instead of [Hedenb.] [NHRS-HEVA000001137-1138]. Hedenborg visited Rhodes more than once, and these three specimens should have been collected in two different journeys. We consider as holotype the one with a different label (NHRS-HEVA000001129).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="400C6B01FAD37881162006C49AFF28C0" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">
After 
<bibRefCitation id="F4A1ED0F766C62EF6B617A1BE047CE4D" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" refId="B21" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1854. Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta. Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.15890" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta" url="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854)</bibRefCitation>
, all the most important authors considered 
<taxonomicName id="CF5584B963ECA0187036B5FE2022D1B2" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum wesmaeli" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wesmaeli">
<emphasis id="016BC5FFFD7F1D08A7DFD9866FDED5DF" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum wesmaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="494DAF24977CBDF25FA14F1C9F8AE395" baseAuthorityName="Foerster" baseAuthorityYear="1771" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum cyanurum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cyanurum">
<emphasis id="6B14ECB2150C518550AF2F780794E585" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum cyanurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Forster, 1771) (
<bibRefCitation id="455EC060B08AAE66A1E87C065522B098" author="Mocsary, A" journalOrPublisher="Hungarian Academy of Sciences, Budapest" pageId="46" pageNumber="125" refId="B62" refString="Mocsary, A, 1889. Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrestris Universi. Hungarian Academy of Sciences, Budapest" title="Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrestris Universi." year="1889">
<normalizedToken id="A9D36258AF3C715B113B9F923FF065B1" originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
1889
</bibRefCitation>
: 190; 
<bibRefCitation id="853247DF2EF5D8FEB0489256D14E77E4" author="Dalla Torre, CG de" journalOrPublisher="Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Chrysididae (Tubulifera)" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" refId="B23" refString="Dalla Torre, CG de, 1892. . Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Chrysididae (Tubulifera) vol. 6" volume="vol. 6" year="1892">Dalla Torre 1892</bibRefCitation>
: 38; Bishoff 1913: 26; 
<bibRefCitation id="14DAACBEA2A92DD11B3C0662B82BDCE7" author="Trautmann, W" journalOrPublisher="Uschman, Weimar" pageId="48" pageNumber="127" refId="B101" refString="Trautmann, W, 1927. Die Goldwespen Europas. Uschman, Weimar" title="Die Goldwespen Europas." year="1927">Trautmann 1927</bibRefCitation>
: 80; 
<bibRefCitation id="23092330E6DFC83431A279C83E654669" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 110" refId="B44" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1951. Die europaeischen Chrysididen (Hymenoptera). Versuch einer natuerlichen Ordnung mit Diagnosen. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 24 (1): 1 - 110" title="Die europaeischen Chrysididen (Hymenoptera). Versuch einer natuerlichen Ordnung mit Diagnosen." volume="24" year="1951">Linsenmaier 1951</bibRefCitation>
: 107). However, it was not even mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="345692EA3D5A96D4D4218371B769275C" author="Mader, L" journalOrPublisher="Entomologischer Anzeiger" pageId="46" pageNumber="125" pagination="125 - 126" refId="B52" refString="Mader, L, 1933. Etwas ueber Hymenopteren. Entomologischer Anzeiger 13: 125 - 126" title="Etwas ueber Hymenopteren." volume="13" year="1933">Mader (1933)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EAD18995A631818B8D5449CEAAC988EF" author="Zimmermann, S" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte" pageId="48" pageNumber="127" pagination="645 - 42" refId="B104" refString="Zimmermann, S, 1937. Ueber die Verbreitung und Formenbildung der Gattung Stilbum Spin. (Chrysididae, Hymenopt.). Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 6: 645 - 42" title="Ueber die Verbreitung und Formenbildung der Gattung Stilbum Spin. (Chrysididae, Hymenopt.)." volume="6" year="1937">Zimmermann (1937)</bibRefCitation>
in their revisions of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="599B1D99C706EFEE1D49485EECE8E426" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F10EE5CB74772F6A52D52CAE4BDA11A2" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In his major revisions, 
<bibRefCitation id="AD42E6B75B2A7341CEC3E7EDD6DB82B5" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 232" refId="B45" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1959. Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">Linsenmaier (1959</bibRefCitation>
: 181 and 
<bibRefCitation id="7BFE45E72811378A008A41B47EEC4F95" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 144" refId="B46" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1968. Revision der Familie Chrysididae Zweiter Nachtrag. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 41 (1-4): 1 - 144" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae Zweiter Nachtrag." volume="41" year="1968">1968</bibRefCitation>
: 123) used the name 
<taxonomicName id="C0C4F44DCDFD41B6865A035D1696C510" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens subsp. subcalens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="calens" subSpecies="subcalens">Stilbum calens ssp. subcalens</taxonomicName>
Mader, 1933 (invalid name because described as 
<emphasis id="2408E9EF5FBBDC1A2DD38DE875911A53" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">aberratio</emphasis>
) in place of 
<taxonomicName id="BC396990F66466974715D7DD7410163F" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum wesmaeli" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wesmaeli">
<emphasis id="68A02DA47E071F8EA0D5A4C2BFB204A0" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum wesmaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the corresponding subspecies distributed in the Mediterranean basin (Dalmatia, Balcan Contries, Rhodes, Persia, southern Switzerland (Misox), southern France, Spanien, northern Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="EC803751CDACFCCEAFFEFD7C780CB064" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 232" refId="B45" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1959. Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">Linsenmaier 1959</bibRefCitation>
) and Lebanon (
<bibRefCitation id="31565D6228070A718997000426E32CEE" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 144" refId="B46" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1968. Revision der Familie Chrysididae Zweiter Nachtrag. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 41 (1-4): 1 - 144" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae Zweiter Nachtrag." volume="41" year="1968">Linsenmaier 1968</bibRefCitation>
)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC66E7A94F35EBA3828362ECBA309E19" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">
In the last publications, 
<bibRefCitation id="8A7D757303239F961B83F14F2B81DEE1" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="245 - 300" refId="B48" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1997a. Altes und Neues von den Chrysididen (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Entomofauna 18 (19): 245 - 300" title="Altes und Neues von den Chrysididen (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volume="18" year="1997 a">Linsenmaier (1997a</bibRefCitation>
: 287, 
<bibRefCitation id="DB7836C1E793973ABB3BE0BF4F6A7219" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B49" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1997b. Die Goldwespen der Schweiz. Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer 9" title="Die Goldwespen der Schweiz." volume="9" year="1997 b">1997b</bibRefCitation>
: 134, 
<bibRefCitation id="F5B7B1E0CECC7FDE60B33B42145F993C" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B50" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1999. Die Goldwespen Nordafrikas (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). In: Entomofauna." title="Die Goldwespen Nordafrikas (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volumeTitle="Entomofauna." year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
: 254) used 
<taxonomicName id="8D60C3CE6A155581EACB6E58B14C2809" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens subsp. wesmaeli" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="calens" subSpecies="wesmaeli">Stilbum calens ssp. wesmaeli</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom as the oldest name for this species, synonymizing 
<taxonomicName id="B3401321329787861C83DAFAD28100D5" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum subcalens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subcalens">
<emphasis id="D1B8F95C227F43C2791F338DC513F87D" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum subcalens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5B376BBECCE79AD1FE8D54DFB153AFEC" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum macedonicum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="macedonicum">
<emphasis id="7F76A7448A34EB1AB63535B45BCE7FEC" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum macedonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Trautmann, 1926 with 
<taxonomicName id="AB41273BC4AB3E564C426E4D07010F20" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens subsp. wesmaeli" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="calens" subSpecies="wesmaeli">Stilbum calens ssp. wesmaeli</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="BD9B3C04BA2A379F89247BED8CFD2C99" author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 232" refId="B45" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1959. Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 1 - 232" title="Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der europaeischen Spezies." volume="32" year="1959">Linsenmaier (1959)</bibRefCitation>
treated the invalid name 
<taxonomicName id="8D8773B1A65BC9522A0481F30C674AA6" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="subcalens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subcalens">
<emphasis id="FA6692554D7ECE316A4B235882D9967B" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">subcalens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="6BA7572A41329AC37DE838451CBD91CA" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="calens">
<emphasis id="DB7314456F908E047C8479DF4ADB1A94" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum calens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and thus made this name available as species-group name (ICZN 1999, article 45.6.3.). As Linsenmaier was the first author to make the name available, he should be considered as the author of 
<taxonomicName id="EB79CAF11C00C7A146CCF9FEE87B5121" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum subcalens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subcalens">
<emphasis id="31C82CE78327009A8CB4E3C220A8D6CA" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum subcalens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ICZN 1999, article 50.3.1.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D88A1419F3B878305AAC7CDFBF0B071" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">
The type and the other specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="87CF6E4F6F739F0472A82BC640017543" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum wesmaeli" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wesmaeli">
<emphasis id="053CFEDEA368AAFFAFF0B1E38023CF32" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum wesmaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in NHRS are not related to 
<taxonomicName id="FC27044E26AE8BA929F6093031463F1B" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="calens">
<emphasis id="4E3A4C695F15667C4B269D6200F638F2" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum calens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius), but belong to a different population of 
<taxonomicName id="8741F07FD1C2C8E911FEAB98ABF03813" baseAuthorityName="Foerster" baseAuthorityYear="1771" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum cyanurum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="116" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cyanurum">
<emphasis id="B09EAA59CA182C34193149A1CEC72A55" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">Stilbum cyanurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Forster) probably endemic to the island. 
<bibRefCitation id="175E4ECA4D2E18E0C2D00C2CB05FD009" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Berlingianis, Lund" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" refId="B19" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1845. Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano. Berlingianis, Lund, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.66977" title="Dispositio Methodica Specierum Hymenopterorum, secundum Familias Insectorum Naturales. Part. II. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano." url="10.5962/bhl.title.66977" year="1845">Dahlbom (1845</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0A350B1D68ADF91F94595FCF6691B791" author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="44" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" refId="B21" refString="Dahlbom, AG, 1854. Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta. Tip. F. Nicolai, Berlin, DOI: 10.5962/bhl.title.15890" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis. Specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per Familias, Genera, Species et Varietates disposita atque descripta" url="10.5962/bhl.title.15890" year="1854">1854</bibRefCitation>
) descriptions are clear and this species is easily identifiable by the typical shape of the metanotal protrusion, which is deeply bilobed (&quot; 
<emphasis id="77893A3DB4F669CAE93D03E1AC62858F" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="116">postscutelli processus emarginatus</emphasis>
&quot;). All the specimens from Rhodes show this special feature, and for this reason we consider this isolated population as a possible valid subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
